###
### jEdit hints
### By Slava Pestov <sp@gjt.org>
###

tip.0=These tips can be disabled in the File->Global Options dialog
tip.1=Press C+d C+d to delete the current line
tip.2=Press C+d C+s to delete from the start of the current line to the caret
tip.3=Press C+d C+f to delete from the caret to the end of the current line
tip.4=Try File->Open URL to fetch files via ftp & http
tip.5=The last 25 pasted strings are listed in the Edit->Paste Previous dialog
tip.6=The Buffers menu displays (modified) next to files that have changed
tip.7=Try File->Send to send the current file via e-mail
tip.8=jEdit performs syntax highlighting when printing, too
tip.9=Try disabling syntax highlighting to speed jEdit up a bit
tip.10=The -nosplash command line switch makes jEdit start a little faster
tip.11=To go to the beginning or end of the buffer, press HOME and END 3 times
tip.12=The Escape key does the equivalent of pushing Cancel in a dialog
tip.13=The Enter key does the equivalent of pushing OK in a dialog
tip.14=Tab and Shift+Tab shift to the next and previous element in a dialog
tip.15=Give the Search->HyperSearch command a go sometime
tip.16=Press C+t to save the current position, and C+y to go back to it later
tip.17=C+LEFT and C+RIGHT move to the previous and next word, respectively
tip.18=C+UP and C+DOWN move to the previous and next paragraph, respectively
tip.19=Pressing Shift with an arrow key extends the selection in that direction
tip.20=A+LEFT and A+RIGHT shift a block of text left or right by one Tab
tip.21=Use markers to move around large documents
tip.22=The Open URL command isn't just for URLs: file names can be entered too
tip.23=The Save To URL command isn't just for URLs: file names can be entered too
tip.24=Try Edit->Format Text to make text look "nicer"
tip.25=C+x, C+c and C+v work in all text fields, not just the main editor
tip.26=jEdit home page: <http://www.gjt.org/~sp/jedit.html>
tip.27=If the caret is after a bracket, C+] will go to the matching one
tip.28=C+[ selects the current code block ( { ... } )
tip.29=Press F10 and use the arrow keys for mouse-free menu operation
tip.30=Undo and Redo remember the last 100 editing actions
tip.31=Try Edit->Tabs to Spaces if you do not like using Tabs
tip.32=Try Edit->Spaces to Tabs if someone sent you a file with soft tabs
tip.33=jEdit can transparently edit GZipped files
tip.34=Power users: edit jedit_gui.props to change the menu bar
tip.35=You can change menu item shortcuts in File->Global Options->Shortcuts
tip.36=jEdit is Open Source: give copies to your friends
tip.37=jEdit is Open Source: you can edit the source code to suit your needs
tip.38=Files can be opened read only for browsing with the -readonly switch
tip.39=When started with no parameters, jEdit opens files from the last session
tip.40=Menus and menu items can be selected with A+<underlined char>
tip.41=Markers are saved across editing sessions to .<filename>.marks
tip.42=If jEdit crashes, look in #<filename># for autosaved data
tip.43=When saving, jEdit first backs the file up to <filename>~
tip.44=Use File->New View to create a new editor window
tip.45=Auto indent coolness: press Tab on an indented line to insert a real Tab
tip.46=When editing HTML files, use File->Open Selection to check links
tip.47=To select lots of text, press C+t at the start and C+u at the end
tip.48=You can have more than one view editing a buffer (File->New View)
tip.49=Press F1 for help
tip.50=The window size is saved between editing sessions
tip.51=File->Open Recent contains up to 8 previously opened file names
tip.52=jEdit can be customized to your needs in the File->Global Options dialog
tip.53=Mac users: jEdit uses Mac-style shortcuts: C+z, C+x, C+c, C+v, etc
tip.54=Windows users: try selecting the Windows L&F in the Options dialog
tip.55=CDE/Motif users: try selecting the Motif L&F in the Options dialog
tip.56=Mac users: try selecting the MacOS L&F in the Options dialog
tip.57=To GZip the current file, do a Save As to <filename>.gz
tip.58=HTML mode colorizes JavaScripts in <script> tags - try it!
tip.59=If jEdit crashes during an autosave, you can still recover your file
tip.60=Press C+e C+j to center the current line on the screen
tip.61=Double click on a bracket to select the code block it delimits
tip.62=C+t saves the current position, C+k flips between it and the caret
tip.63=C+i will go to the first non-whitespace character of the current line
tip.64=If you prefer soft tabs, specify so in the Options dialog
tip.65=Try out the commenting commands in Edit->Code Block Operations
tip.66=Regexp coolness: $1-$9 inserts the contents of subexpression 1-9
tip.67=Use UP/DOWN to recall the last 25 search & replace strings
tip.68=Use Edit->Paste Predefined to insert frequently used strings
tip.69=Try File->Save All Buffers to save all open files
tip.70=A block caret can be enabled in File->Global Options->Editor
tip.71=Use File->Reload to reload the current file from disk
tip.72=Try right clicking on the text area
tip.73=The tool bar can be disabled in File->Global Options->General
tip.74=Quoted literals that don't end on the same line are shown differently
tip.75=HTML entities that don't end on the same line are shown differently
tip.76=The tab size can be set on a buffer-specific basis in File->Buffer Options
tip.77=F11 and F12 open the previous and next buffer, respectively
tip.78=The File->Buffer Options dialog sets properties on a per-buffer basis
tip.79=If you prefer Indent on Enter, enable it in File->Global Options->Editor
tip.80=The help viewer can be used as a simple WWW browser
tip.81=You can change the default edit mode in File->Global Options->Editor
tip.82=Check out the jEdit plugin central <http://www.icg-online.de/jedit/>
tip.83=Pressing Insert toggles overwrite mode
tip.84=jEdit supports both literal and regular expression search & replace
tip.85=jEdit supports multi file search and replace
tip.86=Change plugin settings in File->Plugin Options
tip.87=EOL markers can be disabled in File->Global Options->Editor
tip.88=To go to the first and last visible character, press HOME HOME and END END
